  "text": "Using data from a Kaiser Permanente \"real-world\" study, cost-effectiveness of SMBG one and three times per day was modeled. For both SMBG frequencies, relative risks (versus no SMBG) were lower for most complications. Although not cost-saving, both SMBG frequencies showed good value. Incremental costeffectiveness ratios were less than $8,000 per quality-adjusted life-year gained [CITATION_1] .",
